com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.morseunits

Interface PlayableMorseUnit

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SymbolSetBase.MorseSymbol
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Element

    public interface PlayableMorseUnit
    A set of dots and dashes that can be played back. Callers must supply a timing specification and action interfaces that create the dits and dahs themselves.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void play(OnOff stateSetter, Delayer delayer, MorseTiming standard)
      Play back this set of dots and dashes.

    • Method Detail

      • play

        void play(OnOff stateSetter,
          Delayer delayer,
          MorseTiming standard)
   throws java.lang.Exception
        Play back this set of dots and dashes. Gaps within this set of dots and dashes, in some contexts including trailing spacing, are also played.
        Parameters:
        stateSetter - switch to control the indicator that creates dits and dahs
        delayer - timer that provides the process of waiting between state transitions
        standard - timing with which to play back the dits and dahs
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if stateSetter or delayer causes an exception during operation
        Since:
        1.0
